---
description: Respect user-owned product testing and avoid unsolicited browser/screenshot validation
alwaysApply: true
---

# Validation Ownership

- If the user says they will test the product, do not run browser automation, take screenshots, or perform visual QA unless they explicitly ask.
- For backend readiness questions, validate through code review, schema/data inspection, logs, build/type checks, and targeted API or database commands.
- When UI testing could be useful, state what the user should verify manually instead of launching browser tools.
- Keep status updates focused on what was verified, what remains uncertain, and the next concrete backend/product steps.
- Do not treat screenshots as proof that backend changes are correct; verify backend behavior from the pipeline, database rows, and function responses.
